00:01:34,220 --> 00:01:36,980
=Go! Beach Volleyball Girls=

17
00:01:37,060 --> 00:01:39,980
=Episode 11=

18
00:01:41,980 --> 00:01:45,380
(Occupied, Xingang Haibo)

19
00:01:50,540 --> 00:01:51,480
Come on. You two.

20
00:01:51,860 --> 00:01:53,120
A captain and a team doctor.

21
00:01:53,780 --> 00:01:55,540
It's natural to care for teammates.

22
00:01:55,540 --> 00:01:56,860
But why drag me into this?

23
00:01:56,860 --> 00:01:58,620
Aren't you part of our team?

24
00:01:58,620 --> 00:02:00,080
I'm not the only one on the team.

25
00:02:00,320 --> 00:02:01,370
Because Lang Yueting has caused

26
00:02:01,370 --> 00:02:02,860
a psychological shadow for Weilan.

27
00:02:02,860 --> 00:02:04,020
You and Lang Yueting are...

28
00:02:04,020 --> 00:02:05,080
We don't want to know

29
00:02:05,080 --> 00:02:06,180
about your relationship with her.

30
00:02:06,540 --> 00:02:08,090
But you're the best in our team.

31
00:02:08,090 --> 00:02:09,200
We need you to solve this problem.

32
00:02:10,340 --> 00:02:11,180
Yeah.

33
00:02:11,190 --> 00:02:12,820
You're the star player.

34
00:02:12,820 --> 00:02:13,680
You're better than anyone.

35
00:02:14,580 --> 00:02:15,680
You guys are just kidding around.

36
00:02:16,020 --> 00:02:17,280
Gao, we can't do this without you.

37
00:02:25,780 --> 00:02:26,920
Coming, coming.

38
00:02:27,420 --> 00:02:28,700
- Grandpa, hello!
- Grandpa, hello!

39
00:02:28,700 --> 00:02:29,540
And you are?

40
00:02:30,780 --> 00:02:32,300
I recognize this young lady.

41
00:02:32,300 --> 00:02:34,280
Aren't you Weilan's roommate?

42
00:02:34,620 --> 00:02:35,700
Yes, Grandpa.

43
00:02:35,700 --> 00:02:36,580
What's your name again?

44
00:02:36,580 --> 00:02:37,820
I'm Li Guoduo.

45
00:02:37,820 --> 00:02:39,440
Yes, yes, Li Guoduo.

46
00:02:40,460 --> 00:02:41,980
- Here to see Weilan?
- Yes, we're here to see her.

47
00:02:41,980 --> 00:02:43,240
- Is Weilan home?
- Yes, yes.

48
00:02:43,300 --> 00:02:44,300
Come in.

49
00:02:44,300 --> 00:02:45,780
- Grandpa, I'm Shao Nian.
- Hello, hello.

50
00:02:45,780 --> 00:02:47,440
- Grandpa, I'm Gao Ge.
- Hello, hello, hello.

51
00:02:49,380 --> 00:02:50,220
Alright.

52
00:02:50,220 --> 00:02:52,040
Please sit.

53
00:02:52,420 --> 00:02:53,520
You all sit here for a bit.

54
00:02:53,820 --> 00:02:54,780
I'll go call her.

55
00:02:54,780 --> 00:02:55,640
She's still asleep.

56
00:02:55,870 --> 00:02:56,920
She's always sleeping these days.

57
00:02:57,780 --> 00:02:58,940
Sit for a while.

58
00:02:58,940 --> 00:02:59,780
- Thank you, Grandpa.
- Sure.

59
00:03:03,140 --> 00:03:03,980
Weilan,

60
00:03:03,980 --> 00:03:04,820
wake up.

61
00:03:06,380 --> 00:03:07,220
Get up.

62
00:03:07,540 --> 00:03:08,840
Friends are here to see you.

63
00:03:10,100 --> 00:03:10,940
Get up.

64
00:03:11,820 --> 00:03:13,820
Weilan's grandpa's house is so beautiful.

65
00:03:13,820 --> 00:03:14,800
The environment is so nice.

66
00:03:15,220 --> 00:03:16,240
It's quite lovely.

67
00:03:16,460 --> 00:03:17,560
But the house

68
00:03:17,820 --> 00:03:18,680
seems quite old.

69
00:03:19,020 --> 00:03:19,860
Weilan.

70
00:03:21,660 --> 00:03:22,560
Get up.

71
00:03:24,180 --> 00:03:26,280
- Let's go check.
- Stop sleeping. Get up.

72
00:03:29,020 --> 00:03:29,860
Weilan.

73
00:03:30,380 --> 00:03:31,920
Duoduo and the others are here to see you.

74
00:03:32,740 --> 00:03:34,480
Grandpa, let me take a look.

75
00:03:36,340 --> 00:03:37,180
Weilan.

76
00:03:38,980 --> 00:03:40,600
Grandpa, she's not here.

77
00:03:43,260 --> 00:03:44,780
She was just sleeping here.

78
00:03:44,780 --> 00:03:46,120
But now she's gone.

79
00:03:47,540 --> 00:03:48,380
Weilan?

80
00:03:48,860 --> 00:03:49,700
Weilan?

81
00:03:50,340 --> 00:03:51,180
Grandpa.

82
00:03:52,180 --> 00:03:53,700
Are these all Weilan's awards?

83
00:03:53,700 --> 00:03:54,540
Yes.

84
00:03:54,660 --> 00:03:56,480
These are all hers.

85
00:03:56,900 --> 00:03:58,680
(Advanced Award, Certificate of Honor)
- Weilan has been

86
00:03:58,780 --> 00:04:00,240
very independent since she was little.

87
00:04:00,540 --> 00:04:03,120
She's very proud and competitive.

88
00:04:03,300 --> 00:04:05,320
(Certificate of Award, First Place)
Her mind is also very simple.

89
00:04:05,980 --> 00:04:07,620
Anything she sets her mind on,

90
00:04:07,620 --> 00:04:09,200
she has to do it perfectly.

91
00:04:11,340 --> 00:04:13,600
She didn't have many friends growing up.

92
00:04:13,980 --> 00:04:15,280
People who don't understand her

93
00:04:15,500 --> 00:04:16,840
think she's arrogant.

94
00:04:18,170 --> 00:04:19,010
But really,

95
00:04:19,340 --> 00:04:21,110
she needs understanding and companionship.

96
00:04:21,380 --> 00:04:22,880
We all understand that.

97
00:04:26,450 --> 00:04:28,590
(National High School Volleyball Tournament)
She won this trophy

98
00:04:28,590 --> 00:04:30,200
(MVP)
in her first year of high school.

99
00:04:31,220 --> 00:04:33,180
She's rarely lost on the court

100
00:04:33,180 --> 00:04:34,800
since she was young.

101
00:04:35,700 --> 00:04:37,680
Especially her powerful spikes.

102
00:04:38,340 --> 00:04:39,500
They're impressive, right?

103
00:04:39,500 --> 00:04:40,540
She won this trophy

104
00:04:40,540 --> 00:04:41,600
with that move.

105
00:04:42,740 --> 00:04:43,580
Truly impressive.

106
00:04:44,580 --> 00:04:46,480
Okay, you all wait here.

107
00:04:46,740 --> 00:04:48,460
I'll go find her. She won't have gone far.

108
00:04:48,460 --> 00:04:49,300
- Alright.
- Sure.

109
00:04:50,780 --> 00:04:51,620
Weilan?

110
00:04:53,380 --> 00:04:54,220
Weilan?

111
00:04:55,540 --> 00:04:56,380
Bro.

112
00:04:57,260 --> 00:04:58,160
I shouldn't have come.

113
00:04:58,900 --> 00:05:00,280
She must've heard my voice.

114
00:05:01,420 --> 00:05:02,680
Chen Weilan isn't that sensitive.

115
00:05:03,500 --> 00:05:04,340
Don't overthink it.

116
00:05:06,900 --> 00:05:09,390
(Chen Weilan won first place in the First
Xingang City Beach Volleyball Game)

117
00:05:09,390 --> 00:05:12,540
(Beijing No.8 High School Volleyball Club,
Advanced Award)

118
00:05:39,860 --> 00:05:40,840
Found her.

119
00:05:41,180 --> 00:05:42,020
Don't worry.

120
00:05:49,300 --> 00:05:50,320
So, you are here.

121
00:05:51,540 --> 00:05:53,320
Do you know how long we looked for you?

122
00:05:54,100 --> 00:05:55,040
Why were you looking for me?

123
00:05:56,100 --> 00:05:57,160
After your training that day,

124
00:05:57,580 --> 00:05:58,960
you came to your grandpa's house,

125
00:05:59,260 --> 00:06:00,720
and disappeared.

126
00:06:01,860 --> 00:06:02,880
Do you know that I...

127
00:06:03,500 --> 00:06:05,120
we were very worried about you?

128
00:06:06,100 --> 00:06:07,620
I'm an adult now.

129
00:06:07,620 --> 00:06:08,720
What could possibly happen?

130
00:06:09,540 --> 00:06:10,680
We were just concerned about you.

131
00:06:11,940 --> 00:06:13,400
What's there to worry about?

132
00:06:15,580 --> 00:06:17,240
I just got tired from practice,

133
00:06:17,580 --> 00:06:18,820
so I wanted some rest.

134
00:06:18,820 --> 00:06:20,440
I came here to have a meal with my grandpa.

135
00:06:21,020 --> 00:06:22,780
Do I need to report everything to you?

136
00:06:22,780 --> 00:06:24,180
Chen Weilan,

137
00:06:24,180 --> 00:06:25,880
people are worried about you. Please cooperate.

138
00:06:26,460 --> 00:06:28,040
How long has it been since you trained?

139
00:06:28,660 --> 00:06:29,940
Come back and continue training with us.

140
00:06:31,020 --> 00:06:32,340
Do I need to report

141
00:06:32,340 --> 00:06:33,980
whether I train or not?

142
00:06:33,980 --> 00:06:35,200
I'm practicing every day.

143
00:06:40,100 --> 00:06:41,300
Don't take what Li Guoduo said

144
00:06:41,300 --> 00:06:42,300
on the beach volleyball court

145
00:06:42,300 --> 00:06:43,360
too seriously.

146
00:06:44,100 --> 00:06:45,560
She really wants to help you.

147
00:06:46,380 --> 00:06:47,560
You know how she is.

148
00:06:48,380 --> 00:06:49,500
She's impulsive

149
00:06:49,500 --> 00:06:50,600
and thoughtless.

150
00:06:53,220 --> 00:06:54,060
But I have to say.

151
00:06:54,060 --> 00:06:55,640
She's right.

152
00:06:56,140 --> 00:06:57,880
Your problem is because of Lang Yueting.

153
00:07:00,460 --> 00:07:01,920
What does this have to do with her?

154
00:07:03,700 --> 00:07:05,260
In the National Youth Team tryout,

155
00:07:05,260 --> 00:07:06,860
Lang Yueting won the MVP.

156
00:07:06,860 --> 00:07:07,740
This has always been

157
00:07:07,740 --> 00:07:09,160
a knot in your heart, right?

158
00:07:12,180 --> 00:07:13,700
Bro, you're obsessed with her,

159
00:07:13,700 --> 00:07:15,000
but please be rational.

160
00:07:16,460 --> 00:07:18,480
She won the MVP in that match,

161
00:07:18,860 --> 00:07:19,940
but the one who won was me.

162
00:07:19,940 --> 00:07:21,440
I won that match.

163
00:07:27,420 --> 00:07:29,240
We watched the video of your match.

164
00:07:29,780 --> 00:07:30,620
I reviewed

165
00:07:30,620 --> 00:07:32,640
every detail carefully.

166
00:07:34,220 --> 00:07:36,040
Every time Lang Yueting blocked,

167
00:07:36,340 --> 00:07:37,640
you weren't in your best form.

168
00:07:37,900 --> 00:07:40,160
You couldn't spike the ball successfully.

169
00:07:40,820 --> 00:07:41,740
And this was just like

170
00:07:41,740 --> 00:07:43,400
your performance the other day.

171
00:07:44,260 --> 00:07:45,780
- So?
- Chen Weilan.

172
00:07:46,140 --> 00:07:47,060
Volleyball

173
00:07:47,060 --> 00:07:47,900
is about winning.

174
00:07:48,740 --> 00:07:50,640
But before you beat others,

175
00:07:51,140 --> 00:07:53,280
you have to beat yourself first.

176
00:08:00,900 --> 00:08:01,740
Finished?

177
00:08:13,060 --> 00:08:14,140
Here we are.

178
00:08:14,140 --> 00:08:15,460
- Grandpa, Grandpa.
- Grandpa.

179
00:08:15,460 --> 00:08:17,140
Come on, everyone. Sit at the table.

180
00:08:17,140 --> 00:08:17,980
Let me serve, Grandpa.

181
00:08:18,180 --> 00:08:19,460
- No problem.
- Let me do it.

182
00:08:19,460 --> 00:08:21,080
- Thank you so much.
- Be careful. It's hot.

183
00:08:21,240 --> 00:08:22,640
- Thank you, Grandpa.
- Careful with your hand.

184
00:08:22,820 --> 00:08:24,000
- Careful.
- Well.

185
00:08:24,580 --> 00:08:25,860
Let's not wait for them.

186
00:08:25,860 --> 00:08:26,940
Let's start eating, okay?

187
00:08:26,940 --> 00:08:29,580
It's alright, Grandpa. He found Weilan,
and they are coming back.

188
00:08:29,580 --> 00:08:30,680
- Found her?
- Yes.

189
00:08:32,500 --> 00:08:33,760
Speak of the devil, here they are.

190
00:08:34,020 --> 00:08:35,120
Where did you go?

191
00:08:35,380 --> 00:08:36,950
Everyone's been looking for you.

192
00:08:37,500 --> 00:08:38,900
I just went for a walk.

193
00:08:38,900 --> 00:08:40,120
Who knew they would come?

194
00:08:40,420 --> 00:08:41,950
Alright, take a seat.

195
00:08:42,180 --> 00:08:43,020
- Okay.
- Well.

196
00:08:43,020 --> 00:08:44,720
I've prepared many dishes today.

197
00:08:45,340 --> 00:08:46,180
Duoduo.

198
00:08:46,540 --> 00:08:48,260
This is the steamed crab

199
00:08:48,260 --> 00:08:49,380
you smelled earlier.

200
00:08:49,380 --> 00:08:50,330
- Thank you, Grandpa.
- It's fresh.

201
00:08:50,330 --> 00:08:51,700
- Try some.
- It smells amazing.

202
00:08:51,700 --> 00:08:52,740
I wanted to eat it earlier.

203
00:08:52,740 --> 00:08:54,380
You have some too. It's definitely delicious.

204
00:08:54,380 --> 00:08:55,540
- Here.
- Look at that.

205
00:08:55,540 --> 00:08:57,320
Look how easygoing Duoduo is.

206
00:08:57,540 --> 00:08:58,380
Learn from her.

207
00:08:58,740 --> 00:09:00,800
No, Grandpa, she's more easygoing than me.

208
00:09:01,860 --> 00:09:02,840
Come on. Eat up.

209
00:09:03,380 --> 00:09:04,340
Young man,

210
00:09:04,340 --> 00:09:05,580
you're too thin.

211
00:09:05,580 --> 00:09:07,220
Eat more. Get some nutrition.

212
00:09:07,220 --> 00:09:08,300
- Okay, Grandpa.
- Eat more.

213
00:09:08,300 --> 00:09:09,140
Grandpa, join us.

214
00:09:09,140 --> 00:09:10,420
No worries. I have two more dishes.

215
00:09:10,420 --> 00:09:11,260
They'll be ready soon.

216
00:09:11,580 --> 00:09:12,960
Make sure everyone eats well.

217
00:09:13,220 --> 00:09:14,380
You all eat first.

218
00:09:14,380 --> 00:09:15,780
- Grandpa, thank you.
- Thank you, Grandpa.

219
00:09:15,780 --> 00:09:16,620
Thank you.

220
00:09:16,900 --> 00:09:17,740
Start eating.

221
00:09:22,100 --> 00:09:23,380
You handled

222
00:09:23,380 --> 00:09:24,380
that crab very well.

223
00:09:24,380 --> 00:09:25,220
So meticulous.

224
00:09:25,240 --> 00:09:26,840
No wonder you're in the arts.

225
00:09:27,740 --> 00:09:28,580
Let me tell you.

226
00:09:28,740 --> 00:09:30,120
That's called professional ethics.

227
00:09:30,500 --> 00:09:32,460
If you gave me a needle and thread now,

228
00:09:32,460 --> 00:09:33,420
I could sew it back together

229
00:09:33,420 --> 00:09:34,540
and send it swimming.

230
00:09:34,540 --> 00:09:35,920
- Really?
- No way.

231
00:09:38,660 --> 00:09:39,500
Not eating anymore?

232
00:09:42,740 --> 00:09:44,720
Finally, something I'm better at than you.

233
00:09:45,320 --> 00:09:46,180
Come on.

234
00:09:46,180 --> 00:09:48,000
I find it bothersome to handle.

235
00:10:05,780 --> 00:10:06,620
Thank you.

236
00:10:07,140 --> 00:10:07,980
It's pretty good.

237
00:10:08,380 --> 00:10:10,720
Gao, I want to eat a crab from you.

238
00:10:11,260 --> 00:10:12,120
From me?

239
00:10:12,620 --> 00:10:13,460
Alright.

240
00:10:13,660 --> 00:10:14,580
Then sew one for me.

241
00:10:14,580 --> 00:10:15,420
Sure.

242
00:10:21,420 --> 00:10:22,280
Take a break.

243
00:10:23,900 --> 00:10:24,820
Take a break.

244
00:10:24,820 --> 00:10:25,880
Rest for a while.

245
00:10:32,900 --> 00:10:34,320
- Come on.
- Good for you.

246
00:10:35,180 --> 00:10:36,360
You've improved your skills.

247
00:10:36,820 --> 00:10:37,840
You know how to block now.

248
00:10:38,900 --> 00:10:39,860
It was just luck.

249
00:10:39,860 --> 00:10:41,560
Getting it right once is good enough for me.

250
00:10:42,380 --> 00:10:43,300
But you should

251
00:10:43,300 --> 00:10:44,220
improve your own skills.

252
00:10:44,220 --> 00:10:45,320
Why learn from others?

253
00:10:47,060 --> 00:10:47,900
Actually,

254
00:10:49,500 --> 00:10:50,380
we already know

255
00:10:50,380 --> 00:10:51,880
about you and Lang Yueting.

256
00:10:52,380 --> 00:10:53,220
And

257
00:10:53,940 --> 00:10:55,580
that your hand injury has healed.

258
00:10:55,580 --> 00:10:56,560
We all know.

259
00:10:58,500 --> 00:10:59,740
So,

260
00:10:59,740 --> 00:11:01,240
tell us about your past.

261
00:11:01,980 --> 00:11:03,080
So we can help you.

262
00:11:07,140 --> 00:11:07,980
Weilan,

263
00:11:11,380 --> 00:11:13,800
sharing isn't scary, nor is it shameful.

264
00:11:15,100 --> 00:11:16,140
Look.

265
00:11:16,140 --> 00:11:18,180
You have to face your problems

266
00:11:18,180 --> 00:11:19,800
to have a chance at winning.

267
00:11:20,380 --> 00:11:21,220
Look at me.

268
00:11:21,340 --> 00:11:22,920
To play this match against you,

269
00:11:23,220 --> 00:11:24,220
I've been practicing for a week,

270
00:11:24,220 --> 00:11:25,520
from morning till night.

271
00:11:26,060 --> 00:11:27,520
And you praised me for my progress.

272
00:11:30,540 --> 00:11:31,700
I'm not like you.

273
00:11:31,700 --> 00:11:33,100
I don't know so much about theories

274
00:11:33,100 --> 00:11:34,640
and strategic tactics.

275
00:11:34,860 --> 00:11:35,700
I just know

276
00:11:35,780 --> 00:11:37,360
when facing my weaknesses,

277
00:11:37,580 --> 00:11:39,020
I have to bravely overcome them.

278
00:11:39,020 --> 00:11:40,100
I have to face them,

279
00:11:40,100 --> 00:11:41,460
so I can change

280
00:11:41,460 --> 00:11:42,640
and become stronger.

281
00:11:43,900 --> 00:11:44,740
Weilan,

282
00:11:44,820 --> 00:11:45,740
Guoduo has really done a lot

